125.6	Bear	Bear	Bears are mammals of the family Ursidae. Bears are classified as caniforms, or doglike carnivorans, with the pinnipeds being their closest living relatives. Although there are only eight living species of bear, they are widespread, appearing in a wide variety of habitats throughout the Northern Hemisphere and partially in the Southern Hemisphere. Bears are found in the continents of North America, South America, Europe, and Asia.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ae/Ursus_arctos_-_Norway.jpg/200px-Ursus_arctos_-_Norway.jpg
